This paper discusses a new indicator for ranking publications, which is relevant to several sub-fields of computer science. The use of statistical testing to compare rankings suggests a focus on data analysis and evaluation, which is common in sub-fields such as machine learning (cs.LG), information retrieval (cs.IR), and databases (cs.DB). The mention of publications and rankings also suggests a focus on digital libraries (cs.DL) and social informatics (cs.SI).
